WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:07.800
Hello, my name is Ella Kaye and today I'm going to tell you about rainbowR, a community for LGBTQ plus people who code in R

00:00:08.600 --> 00:00:12.920
Everything I talk about today, you can find out more at rainbowR.org

00:00:15.000 --> 00:00:17.760
At the useR conference in 2017

00:00:17.760 --> 00:00:23.559
I was chatting with the guy who I just met and I mentioned in passing my wife.

00:00:24.639 --> 00:00:25.799
I didn't know it at the time

00:00:25.799 --> 00:00:30.200
But the guy I was speaking to is also gay and it turns out that he was finding

00:00:30.480 --> 00:00:34.320
Socializing at the conference at such a large conference to be rather overwhelming

00:00:34.480 --> 00:00:40.480
But as soon as he knew he was speaking to someone else who's also gay, he felt a sense of camaraderie that he could relax

00:00:41.720 --> 00:00:46.840
from there we got to talking about the possibility for, the need for even, an

00:00:47.759 --> 00:00:53.439
LGBTQ plus community within the broader R community and that's how rainbowR was born

00:00:54.200 --> 00:00:58.240
That was seven years ago. The community is now going to over a hundred people

00:00:59.240 --> 00:01:04.559
From our time together today. I'd like you to take away that and why we exist as a community

00:01:05.040 --> 00:01:08.279
Some of what we do and how you can get involved

00:01:09.519 --> 00:01:12.360
we exist to connect support and promote

00:01:13.199 --> 00:01:20.400
LGBTQ plus people in the R community and to spread awareness of LGBTQ plus issues through data-driven activism

00:01:21.120 --> 00:01:25.519
When it comes to connecting, supporting and promoting people we have two main initiatives

00:01:26.800 --> 00:01:31.279
We run monthly meetups over zoom usually on the fourth Wednesday of the month

00:01:31.919 --> 00:01:38.559
These are really relaxed, friendly, supportive sessions where people come together to chat mostly about R

00:01:39.040 --> 00:01:41.760
It's an opportunity to ask and answer questions

00:01:42.320 --> 00:01:46.800
To demonstrate packages or resources you've come across recently and find helpful

00:01:46.800 --> 00:01:51.120
Or to show and tell your own work in a really supportive setting

00:01:52.400 --> 00:01:56.239
We run a buddy scheme to encourage deeper connections within the community

00:01:56.879 --> 00:02:01.440
Which gives people an opportunity to be randomly paired with a buddy in the community

00:02:02.000 --> 00:02:04.160
We open up every three months a form

00:02:04.720 --> 00:02:09.839
Where if you want a buddy you can fill it in with a little bit of information about yourself and your interests

00:02:10.320 --> 00:02:13.679
We then run an R script which gathers the form responses

00:02:14.479 --> 00:02:20.160
Randomly allocates buddy pairs and then automatically generates and sends emails to each pair

00:02:20.720 --> 00:02:26.000
Where the email is pre-populated with information from the form

00:02:26.800 --> 00:02:30.639
And suggestions of things that you might want to talk about or do together

00:02:31.919 --> 00:02:35.679
We do this because we know it can be nerve-wracking to meet somebody new

00:02:36.559 --> 00:02:38.960
And we want to help get those conversations started

00:02:39.759 --> 00:02:43.440
The next round of the buddy scheme will allocate pairs at the beginning of September

00:02:44.080 --> 00:02:49.279
The sign-up sheet is already open. You can see the website for more details. I'll share the link again at the end

00:02:50.559 --> 00:02:52.559
On to data-driven activism

00:02:53.679 --> 00:02:56.160
We host a repo, Tidy Rainbow

00:02:56.960 --> 00:03:02.160
Which contains data sets with data relevant to LGBTQ plus issues

00:03:02.160 --> 00:03:06.160
The data is there for anybody to use and can be used in a variety of ways

00:03:06.720 --> 00:03:13.919
For example, it can be used to practice data visualization or data analysis along the lines of the Tidy Tuesday project

00:03:14.960 --> 00:03:20.720
Or it can be used to provide example data sets when teaching or writing blog posts

00:03:21.279 --> 00:03:24.080
Something that hopefully will be of interest to allies as well

00:03:25.119 --> 00:03:28.960
We're about to start our first ever book club, the book under discussion

00:03:28.960 --> 00:03:33.679
Is going to be Queer Data, using gender, sex and sexuality data for action by Kevin Guillen

00:03:34.720 --> 00:03:39.360
This book club is open for everyone, LGBTQ plus folks and allies alike

00:03:40.559 --> 00:03:44.399
The book club is going to run in the autumn. There are more details on our website

00:03:45.279 --> 00:03:51.520
If you're LGBTQ plus and would like to join the community, you can do so via the join form accessible via our website

00:03:52.160 --> 00:03:55.600
If you fill that in you will shortly thereafter receive a postcard

00:03:56.000 --> 00:04:01.520
If you fill that in you will shortly thereafter receive a personalized welcome email from a member of the Rainbow R team

00:04:02.160 --> 00:04:06.740
An invitation to the slack group and an opportunity to sign up for our newsletter

00:04:07.759 --> 00:04:09.759
For those of you here at the conference

00:04:10.320 --> 00:04:12.479
There's going to be a lunch tomorrow

00:04:13.279 --> 00:04:18.079
And also on the slack there is a channel specifically for people who are here

00:04:18.320 --> 00:04:21.760
So please do sign the join form if you're interested to get access to that

00:04:22.380 --> 00:04:25.679
Unfortunately, I am not personally at the conference

00:04:26.480 --> 00:04:32.959
But Daniel Soberg is. He's a member of the Rainbow R team. He should be here in this room if you're watching this live

00:04:33.600 --> 00:04:34.799
and

00:04:34.799 --> 00:04:36.799
He's looking forward to meeting you

00:04:36.880 --> 00:04:42.980
So if you're LGBTQ plus and you want to join a vibrant and supportive community of fellow R enthusiasts

00:04:43.760 --> 00:04:49.279
Or you're somebody interested in promoting LGBTQ plus people in the R community and beyond

00:04:49.920 --> 00:04:54.559
Please visit our website rainbowr.org to learn more and get involved

00:04:55.359 --> 00:04:57.779
Thank you very much. I hope to meet you soon

